# Normalize line endings to LF in the repo and on checkout — on every OS,
# including Windows. Without this, GitHub's windows runner checks out text files
# with CRLF (core.autocrlf), and `gofmt -l` then flags every .go file as
# unformatted, failing CI. Forcing LF keeps Windows checkouts byte-identical to
# Linux/macOS.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Belt and suspenders: never normalize known-binary assets.
*.png binary
*.zip binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
